description:
Book: Blueprints Neurology
Authors: Bernard Chang, Frank Drislane, Michael Benatar, Juan A. Acosta, John M. Croom
Now in its Second Edition, Blueprints Neurology covers all the basics needed for a clinical rotation as well as for in-service and board exam preparation. This popular Blueprints book has been refined and updated while keeping the succinct, organized, and concise style and content of the first edition. Blueprints Neurology, Second Edition delivers everything you need for your neurology rotation in the classic, easy-to-follow Blueprints format--now including revised and updated diagnostic and treatment information throughout and updated, expanded sections on imaging, headache, and vascular disease. Seventy-five board-format Q&As with complete correct and incorrect answer explanations are included. Key Points in every section highlight the most important, high-yield information for each topic. A color-enhanced design increases the usefulness of figures and tables. A new appendix of evidence-based resources is included..
